[[File:Fahlerz mit Quarz - Dillenburg, Nassau.jpg|thumb|Fahlore from Dillenburg, Nassau, Germany. This piece is from the mineralogical museum in Bonn, Germany.]]
'''Fahlore''', or '''Fahlerz''', refers to an ore consisting of complex [[Sulfosalt minerals|sulfosalts]], mostly the series between [[tennantite]] (Cu<sub>6</sub>[Cu<sub>4</sub>(Fe,Zn)<sub>2</sub>]As<sub>4</sub>S<sub>13</sub>) and [[tetrahedrite]] (Cu<sub>6</sub>[Cu<sub>4</sub>(Fe,Zn)<sub>2</sub>]Sb<sub>4</sub>S<sub>13</sub>). It comes from the German word for pale: Fahl. This refers to the characteristic pale grey to dark black colour.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/6356236|title=Die Namen der Steine : das Mineralreich im Spiegel der Sprache : mit einem Wörterbuch, enthaltend über 1300 Namen von Mineralien, Gesteinen, Edelsteinen, Fabel- und Zaubersteinen|last=1895-|first=Lüschen, Hans,|date=1979|publisher=Ott|isbn=3722562651|edition=2., neubearb. und erw. Aufl|location=Thun|oclc=6356236}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mindat.org/min-1437.html|title=Tennantite-Tetrahedrite Series: Tennantite-Tetrahedrite Series mineral information and data.|website=www.mindat.org|access-date=2018-02-19}}</ref>

