{{Infobox award | name = Royal Society Wolfson Research Merit Grant Award | subheader = | current_awards = | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | description = a five-year salary enhancement to help recruit or retain scientists in the UK | sponsor = {{Plainlist| *[[Royal Society]] *[[Wolfson Foundation]]}} | date = {{Start date|2000}}<ref name="braindrain"/> | location = | country = | presenter = | host = | preshow_host = | acts = | reward = | year = | year2 = | holder = | website = {{URL|http://royalsociety.org/grants/schemes/wolfson-research-merit}} | network = | runtime = | ratings = | producer = | director = | most_awards = | most_nominations = | image2 = | image2size = | alt2 = | caption2 = | previous = | main = | next = }}
The '''Royal Society Wolfson Research Merit Grant Award''' was a grant award originally announced in 2000.<ref name="torygraph">[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1350497/4m-set-aside-to-lure-Beckhams-of-science.html "£4m set aside to lure 'Beckhams of science'"], ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', July 27, 2000.</ref> which has now been superseded by the [[Royal Society Wolfson Fellowship]]s. <ref> {{cite web|url=https://royalsociety.org/grants-schemes-awards/grants/wolfson-research-merit/|title=Royal Society Wolfson Research Merit Award|publisher= Royal Society|accessdate= 26 November 2018}} </ref>
It was administered by the [[Royal Society]] and jointly funded by the [[Wolfson Foundation]] and the UK [[Office of Science and Technology]], to give universities additional financial support to attract key researchers to this country or to retain those who might seek to gain higher salaries elsewhere."<ref>https://www.webcitation.org/6MdvAoJ6d</ref> to tackle the [[brain drain]].<ref name="braindrain"/> They were given in four annual rounds, with up to seven awards per round.<ref name="braindrain">{{Cite journal | last1 = Smaglik | first1 = P. | title = Battling the brain drain | doi = 10.1038/nj6871-03a | journal = Nature | volume = 415 | issue = 6871 | pages = 3–31 | year = 2002 | pmid = 11823808| pmc = }}</ref>
