{{Infobox crater data |titlecolor = |image = Ripley Crater in Color.jpg |caption = Photo of Charon centered on [[Ripley Crater]]. [[Nostromo Chasma]] crosses Ripley vertically. [[Organa (crater)|Organa Crater]] is at 9:00, and Vader is the dark crater at 12:00 |coordinates = {{coord|55|N|15|W|globe:charon_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |coordinates_footnotes = <ref>{{cite web|title=Global map of Charon|url=https://pbs.twimg.com/media/CLNjzEpWgAEpPwJ.jpg:large|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>|globe = Charon |globe_type = moon |quadrangle = |diameter = |depth = |discoverer = ''[[New Horizons]]'' |eponym = [[Darth Vader]] }}
'''Vader''' is the unofficial name given to a dark [[Impact crater|crater]] on [[Pluto]]'s largest [[moon]] [[Charon (moon)|Charon]]. The crater was discovered by [[NASA]]'s ''[[New Horizons]]'' [[space probe]] on its way by Pluto. It was named after [[Darth Vader]] from the ''[[Star Wars]]'' media franchise.
